snippet.textDisplay: Nice pie Babish, here's a quick tip to make it a bit nicer with some practice, when making the crust, dig a well along the outside edge with your index finger, leaving the crust about a fingernails width thick from the edge of the pizza. Next, smooth it out by "poking" the pie with two or three fingers straight down pretty quickly from the outside in. This pops the air bubbles as well as not having the middle part of the dough spread back out over the crust. After that, pick up the pizza with two fingers on each hand and stretch the well you created in the first step, further separating the crust from the middle. Finally, use the slapping stretch method finishing off with one toss. Then you are done and stretching pie like a pro
snippet.textOriginal: Nice pie Babish, here's a quick tip to make it a bit nicer with some practice, when making the crust, dig a well along the outside edge with your index finger, leaving the crust about a fingernails width thick from the edge of the pizza. This pops the air bubbles as well as not having the middle part of the dough spread back out over the crust.
